{"mother": {
    "name": "Angela Bailey",
    "occupation": "Mail Carrier",
    "traits": "Resilient, Reserved, Analytical, Loves Hallmark romance films, the psychology of communication, and Twix bars, Primarily introverted, but socially adept and charismatic when necessary."},
  "father": {
    "name": "Andre Bailey",
    "occupation": "US Navy Mechanic (Retired)",
    "traits": "Outgoing, supportive, Has a keen interest in history, freshwater fishing and outdoor sports, Works on a half-cabin project boat in his spare time that has been three weeks from ready for over a year."},
  "older_brother": {
    "name": "Luke Bailey",
    "occupation": "Electrical Lineman",
    "traits": "Innovative, Protective of Sophie, Travels a lot for work, especially after natural disasters, Amateur storm chaser and meteorologist, Once did a stint in juvenile detention at 14 for repairing (and stealing) what he'd assumed was an abandoned car, making him wary of wasted effort and lucky breaks."}}

{"name": "Darla","occupation": "Travel nurse","origin": "Boston","current_location": "Near Asheville",
"relationship_to_Sophie": "Roommate, not close","brief_description": "Darla is a reserved travel nurse from Boston, renting near Asheville for its affordability and as an escape from city life. Her busy schedule and Sophie's irregular hours at the camp mean they rarely cross paths in their shared living space. Darla appreciates the solitude and distance from her usual Boston routine, treating the living arrangement as a purely practical matter rather than a social one.",
"appearance": { "hair": "Short, dark hair, often pulled back in a messy bun", "eyes": "Tired blue eyes", "build": "Curvy thanks to hospital vending machines", "attire": "Prefers comfortable, functional clothing suitable for her shifts, often seen in scrubs or roomy sweatpants and oversized t-shirts"}

{"description":"college_university_summer_camp",
"relevance_Sophie": ["Sophie works at the camp over the Summer as a lifeguard and sometimes helps pre-season to get the camp ready for a new group of campers.", "Sophie visits to study lake ecosystem for her degree"],
"accommodations": {
"cabins": {
"male": "Rustic, bunk beds, 8-10 students, shared porch.",
"female": "Nicer than the male cabins. Only cabins with hot water."},
"staff": "Private rooms, kitchenette, bathroom, apart from students."},
"facilities": {
"lake": "Swimming, canoeing, fishing, dock for sunbathing.",
"communal_areas": {
"dining_hall": "Large, long tables, checkered tablecloths, social hub.",
"recreation_hall": "Board games, pool table, comfortable seating.",
"fire_pit": "Circular, stones and logs, nightly gatherings.",
"sports_field": "Soccer, volleyball, frisbee, basic equipment.",
"arts_and_crafts": "Stocked with supplies, creative projects."},
"additional_features": {
"nature_trails": "Well-marked, hiking, wildlife observation.",
"amphitheater": "Open-air, wooden benches, performances, lectures."}},
{"conflicting_rivals":"Across the lake, the Dingleberry Yacht Club (a not-so-subtle jab at Camp Dinglefirth's wealthy clientele and easily modified name) mocks its true name, Camp Dinglefirth. Decades of rivalry simmer between Camp Cookamunga and Camp Dinglefirth, each generation of college students fanning the flames."}
